                    <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n2" type="normalized">Zenobis </persName>
                    <floruit notAfter="0290">Early Christian martyr, son (in Ethiopic; in Byzantine: brother) of Zenobia. According to the Byzantine hagiography, Zenobios and his sister Zenobia were from Aegae, Cilicia. Zenobios was a physician and because of his divine healing powers he was consecrated bishop of Aegae. They were tortured and beheaded around 290, during Diocletian's persecutions</floruit>
                    <death>He is commemorated on <date type="diesNatalis" ref="ethiocal:Hedar6">6 (or 7) Ḫǝdār</date> and <date type="diesNatalis" ref="ethiocal:Teqemt9">9 Ṭǝqǝmt</date></death>
                </person>
